rComments: She lectures at a fast but understandable pace. She expected a lot on the midterm but the exam was good. I finished with a low eighty but I had to work hard for it. She's sweet and approachable. She made us write weekly responses to the reading so you have to keep up. Only graded on the online readings for tests not textbook so not a must.

I took Zajac's class in my last year of university. Worst mistake of my university career. She was inexplicably horrible in grading and lecturing. She gave us 50 minutes to do a midterm that had key terms, short answer, and an essay. All in 50 minutes. Her expectations are way too high for undergraduate papers. Mind you, I'm a history major.
